Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; mid brown core; cream slip. Red paint remains? Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p.102, 8. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0067.01. Name Aristarchos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0553)
